    "text": "111th Street, south from 44th Avenue, across the Long Island Railroad tracks. The area on the left, which stretches along the east side of 111th Street, is part of the Corona dumps and later became Flushing Meadow Park where the New York World's Fair of 1939-40 was held.\n\nEugene L. Armbruster Collection\n1923\n",
